    "  {\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Key Insights - Payment Method Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* **Perfect Metric Alignment:** A major analytical finding is that the ranking of payment methods is **nearly identical across both metrics** (Transaction Volume and Total Revenue). Credit Cards dominate, followed by Boleto, Vouchers, and Debit Cards. This strong alignment proves that no single payment method artificially inflates the transaction count with abnormally micro-transactions, nor does any method exclusively handle massive corporate orders.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* **The Credit Engine:** `Credit Card` is the undisputed backbone of Olist's ecosystem. It accounts for **74.0% of all transaction volume** and drives an even higher share of total revenue at **78.5%**. This slight increase indicates that credit card transactions carry a higher average ticket size, confirming that installment options are crucial for high-value purchases in the Brazilian e-commerce market.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* **The Boleto Reality:** `Boleto` (the traditional Brazilian bank slip) solidifies its position as the second most popular method. It captures **19.0% of transactions** and **18.0% of total revenue**, showing it is a stable, reliable channel for credit-conservative customers.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* **Marginal Methods:** `Voucher` (5.5% vol / 2.2% rev) and `Debit Card` (1.5% vol / 1.4% rev) combined make up less than 4% of the platform's revenue, remaining low-impact niche channels.\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"55022c88d0865fc5\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"source\": \"# Part 2: Operational Efficiency & Logistics\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"e1b103a7fa25e596\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 2.1 Logistics Performance\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Business Question:** What is the average delivery time across different Brazilian states, and where do the biggest delays occur?\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"1e77f53217a74c27\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-07-07T18:29:10.486386Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-07-07T18:29:09.877483Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"query = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"SELECT\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    c.customer_state,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (julianday(o.order_delivered_customer_date)-julianday(o.order_purchase_timestamp)) AS delivery_time_days\\n\",\n",
    "    \"FROM orders o\\n\",\n",
    "    \"JOIN customers c ON o.customer_id = c.customer_id\\n\",\n",
    "    \"WHERE o.order_status = 'delivered';\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df_logistics = pd.read_sql_query(query, engine)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df_logistics.head()\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
