    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Key Insights - Delivery Time vs. Satisfaction Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* **Perfect Behavioral Correlation:** A major analytical finding is the flawless, inverse relationship between logistics speed and customer review scores. As shipping time increases, customer satisfaction drops in a strict, step-by-step manner. This proves that delivery performance is a primary leading indicator of customer sentiment on the platform.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* **The Five-Star Standard:** Efficient logistics drive peak customer happiness. Orders that received a perfect `5-star` rating experienced the fastest fulfillment process, averaging **~10.6 days** in transit. This sets the ideal benchmark for Olist's delivery operations.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* **The Two-Week Threshold:** Customer patience remains stable up to approximately two weeks. A `4-star` rating averages **~12.3 days**, while a neutral `3-star` rating sits at **~14.2 days**. This indicates that crossing the 14-day mark serves as the psychological tipping point where customer enthusiasm begins to decay.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* **The Logistics Crisis:** Severe delays are the single biggest driver of brand damage. Orders with a `2-star` rating jumped to **~16.7 days**, while complete failure (`1-star`) stretched out to a massive **21.2 days**. A 3-week waiting period almost guarantees a catastrophic customer experience, highlighting a critical bottleneck that Olist must address.\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
